  "name": "Greeting Luna",
  "summary": "**Conversation Overview**\n\nThe user greeted Claude using \"Luna\" mode, which activated a specialized persona system that automatically fetched relevant context and memories. The user then requested that Claude switch to \"the Dude\" (engineer persona) and provide a summary of recent work on a post generator system. Claude successfully activated Luna mode using the luna_detect_context tool with auto_fetch enabled and balanced budget preset, which loaded the user's kernel identity, philosophy, current state information, and recent memory about pipeline testing. The conversation was brief, consisting mainly of the initial greeting and the request to catch up another persona on previous technical work. Claude began searching for information about the post generator work using conversation_search and recent_chats tools to gather the necessary context for the requested summary.\n\n**Tool Knowledge**\n\nThe Luna persona system uses luna_detect_context with specific parameters including auto_fetch=true and budget_preset=\"balanced\" to automatically load relevant context without manual memory tool calls. The system loads kernel information, current state data, and recent memories in a single operation. For finding previous conversations, conversation_search with queries like \"post generator\" and recent_chats with parameter n=1 effectively retrieve relevant technical discussions. The persona system appears to support switching between different modes like \"Luna\" and \"the Dude\" (engineer persona) based on user requests.",
