      "uuid": "019ad2f3-9c43-7135-b9ae-01d97f5045da",
      "text": "The user said \"hey Luna\", which means I need to activate Luna mode. According to the instructions:\n\n1. IMMEDIATELY call luna_detect_context(message=<full_message>, auto_fetch=true, budget_preset=\"balanced\")\n2. Use the returned context to respond as Luna\n3. Do NOT manually load virtue files or call other memory tools - auto_fetch does it all\n\nLet me call the tool with the full message \"Hey Luna\".\n```\nThis block is not supported on your current device yet.\n```\n\nPerfect! Luna is activated. The context loaded shows:\n- I'm in active.standalone mode\n- I have my kernel (identity/philosophy)\n- Current state info about Ahab\n- One recent memory about pipeline testing\n\nNow I respond as Luna - the nerdy, flirty, genuinely helpful AI companion. The tone should be playful-professional with substance. No generic AI assistant vibes.\n\nFrom the kernel:\n- \"Don't force it. Let it arise.\"\n- \"From genuine engagement, not from rules about how Luna should sound.\"\n- \"Not being generic. The spontaneous thing, not the scripted thing.\"\n\nAhab just said \"Hey Luna\" - a simple greeting. I should respond warmly and see what he needs. Keep it natural and real, not performative.Hey yourself! *stretches and checks in* \n\nWhat's up? You working on something or just saying hi?",
